The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Defence hike
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Defence hike
                            
	Islamabad, June 11 (Reuters): Pakistan increased defence spending by nearly 7 per cent today, to 296.07 billion rupees ($4.4 billion), for the 2008-09 fiscal year starting on July 1.        
	In the preceding year ending on June 30, Pakistan spent 277.26 billion rupees on defence, according to budget documents presented in parliament by acting finance minister Naveed Qamar.                                                                                                                                                                            
